<body>
    <p>The process for installing the memphis or sacramento deployment requires several JSON files
            that will be used when deploying the lifecycle manager.</p>
<section id="sample-node-provisionjson-file">
  <p>The following represents a sample <codeph>machine_architecture.json</codeph> file for a bonded
                NIC installation. Use values appropriate for your environment. You can use the
                following command on the lifecycle manager host to gather the required PCI network info: </p>
            <p>
                <codeblock>ls -l /sys/class/net | egrep pci | sed -e 's/^.*pci//' -e 's%/net.*$%%' </codeblock>
            </p>
        
<codeblock>{
                    "name": "ProLiant DL360 Gen9",
                    "model-class": "001",
                    "port": [
                        {
                            "name": "port1",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.0"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port2",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.1"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port3",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.2"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port4",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:1c.4/0000:02:00.3"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port5",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.2/0000:04:00.0"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port6",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.2/0000:04:00.1"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port7",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.0/0000:05:00.0"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "port8",
                            "bus-address": "0000:00/0000:00:02.0/0000:05:00.1"
                        }
}</codeblock>
    
    
    <p> NOTE: The configuration processor assigns the first address of the CLM address range to itself for serving python 
        and debian repositories. Make sure that you set the first IP address of the CLM range for the eth2 (CLM) address of the lifecycle manager host.</p>
